      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KINGS FURY (9) is suited returning to a venue where he is unbeaten, winning both of his appearances over this distance. Placed from this row when second-up two back at Penrith before a midfield finish at Menangle. Race fit now and can travel in a nice spot from this draw. Has the ability to take this out. MILLWOOD GRACE NZ (4) is looming as a threat after a better effort last start, racing parked but sticking on for second at Parkes. TITIWHA (6) has been producing some good efforts here of late, clocking in fourth from the back line last time and placing from a similar barrier to this three back. Go well. BOLANALONG (7) had been racing consistently before he scored a decisive win last time at this venue, coming from a similar draw and getting home by 10.6 metres in an emphatic display. May feature again.",
